rComments: nina was really helpful, but she goes way too fast to keep up with, has notes online though, so print them out if you don't want to speed copy. uses specific animals so remember them. test is really fair, maybe because of the practice final by the TAs. Quizes in sections every week,  questions to quizes are posted ahead of time so pretty fair.
Her test are straight forward and fair. Her lectures go way too fast so print the lecture notes before class!

20C is taught by two professors, I had D'Amore and Giacommo Bernardi.  D'Amore is alright, lectures are a little fast paced, hard to keep up w/.  Posts skeletal lecture notes and tends to use very specific examples in lecture and used most of them on the final as well.  Provided a good sample final though.

Nina goes really fast in lecture. Print out the outlines and take your own notes as you go through the notes in class. Copy down every example she talks about. E-mail her or  talk to her during her hours before class if something doesn't make sense. She's really nice and helpful. She's very into detail..study hard.
